This message is to announce the availability of Release 19
(25 March 1993 version) of the SU (Seismic UNIX) package.

About SEISMIC UNIX.
The SU package is a pubic domain software package created
at the Center for Wave Phenomena, Colorado School of Mines.
The package may be viewed as an "instant (exploration) 
seismic research and processing environment" for UNIX-based machines.

The package contains tools for:
       reading/writing tapes in the SEG-Y format
       manipulating seismic data in the SEG-Y format
       Fourier transforms
       filtering
       synthetic data generation
       seismic migration
       NMO
       DMO
       PostScript Graphics
       X-windows Graphics

What you need to install the codes:
       You will need a machine running the UNIX operating system.
       The code takes up about 8 megabytes after installation
       and compilation.

The codes have been successfully installed on:
	IBM RS6000
	SUN SPARC STATIONS
	HP 700-800 series machines
	HP Apollo
	NeXT
	Convex

How to get the package: 
       Seismic Unix is obtainable
       via anonymous FTP from  138.67.12.63

The pertinent directory path is     pub/cwpcodes
You will need the following files
        README_BEFORE_UNTARRING
        cwp.tar.Z
        plot.tar.Z
        su.tar.Z
        untar_me_first.tar.Z
        documentation.tar.Z
There are other stand-alone codes in this directory that
may be used with SU.


